01/31/2025,748.343(2)(A) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,03/17/2025,03/20/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium Low,Yes,Operation staff confirmed that another staff had unauthorized access to records.  ,"On 03.20.25 the operation provided the following compliance with all completed documentation to include sign in sheets, training certificates and the training curriculum from 03.05.25:

1.  Boysville will provide INFORMATION SECURITY AND CYBERSECURITY training during our scheduled training week from March 3 to March 7 (Wednesday the March 6, 2025) for all staff with access to TDFPS database systems. This training will cover essential security principles, best practices for password management, email security, social media safety, mobile device security, identity theft protection, and data privacy. It will also focus on the PACES requirement regarding database use, emphasizing that only authorized staff are permitted access and that sharing passwords is strictly prohibited.  Certifications will be issued to demonstrate proof of training and will be sent to the RCM by March 14, 2025. A list of staff members with access to any TDFPS database systems will be provided to the RCM to verify completion of the required training. The list of the staff members will be pulled from Paycom.
	     
2. The CEO, is responsible for developing and implementing the training plan for information security and cybersecurity. After the training is completed, random checks will be conducted to ensure that PACES passwords have not been shared. During these checks, PACES users will be required to sign a confidentiality statement confirming that they have not shared their passwords. 
	 
3. The Performance Quality Improvement (PQI) Safety Chair, will report the results of these checks at the quarterly PQI meeting. The random checks will begin in April, although the exact dates have not yet been determined, coinciding with our next quarterly review. The results of the random checks will be sent to the RCM by April 30,2025.
	 
If a staff member is unable to access any TDFPS database using their password or login ID, they should reach out to the Training Compliance Specialist for help. If the Training Compliance Specialist is unable to resolve the issue, the staff member will be advised to contact the TDFPS help desk or the RCM for further assistance."
